    <p>(SOUNDBITE OF MOVIE, "LOOPER")</p>
    <p>MONDELLO: That's called closing the loop, in this case with young Joe meeting old Joe. And there you have director Rian Johnson's nifty premise.</p>
    <p>"Looper" is plenty of fun on its own, but on Blu-ray, along with the usual commentary tracks, you'll find not two or three, but 22 deleted scenes. There's one that expands a nightclub sequence from the finished film's 12 seconds to well over a minute, including a blink-you'll-miss-it walk-through cameo by Tobey Maguire.</p>
    <p>Another expands a diner conversation between the old and young Joes, explaining a line that flew right by me originally.</p>
